      • sendMail

        public void sendMail(java.lang.String to,
                     java.lang.String cc,
                     java.lang.String reserveDate,
                     java.lang.String startTime,
                     java.lang.String endTime,
                     java.lang.String building,
                     java.lang.String roomNumber,
                     java.lang.String websiteURL)
        Send Email for reservation confirmation. All parameters are string with time in 24-hour format, date in SQL yyyy-MM-dd format, building and room number with String integers, and the website URL to put in the email as a string.
        Parameters:
        to - sendee
        cc - copy other sendees
        reserveDate - reservation start date
        startTime - reservation start time
        endTime - reservation end time
        building - the name of the building where the reservation is made
        roomNumber - room number
        websiteURL - the main URL of the website

                                  java.lang.String websiteURL)
                           throws javax.mail.MessagingException
        This class builds the html email that is being sent to the logged in user as well as the user that they put as the secondary on the reservation.
        Parameters:
        msg - email message contents
        reserveDate - start date of the reservation
        startTime - reservation start time
        endTime - reservation end time
        building - the building where the reservation was made
        roomNumber - room number
        websiteURL - the main URL of the website
        Throws:
        javax.mail.MessagingException - error in sending message Set the message of the email. This is an HTML email message
